{
  "texts": [
    "The 3D trajectories of each action were first represented as curves in ℝ 3 by means of the Square-Root Velocity Function (SRVF; Srivastava et al. 2010).",
    "Then, by normalising the length of curves to 1, the trajectories were represented by points and in a Riemannian manifold, having a spherical structure.",
    "In this space, the social and personal actions were represented by their SRVF curves as q 1 and q 2 respectively.",
    "The distance between q 1 and q 2 on the sphere was used to quantify the similarity between the two curves in ℝ 3.",
    "Indeed, this distance quantifies the amount of deformation in terms of length and height between the two curves."
  ]
}